Iraq Denies Allegations of Detaining Kuwaiti POWs
BAGHDAD , February 27 ( Xinhua ) -- Iraq denied allegations Friday that it still detains Kuwaiti prisoners of war , calling it a new pretext fabricated by the United States in order to prolong the economic sanctions imposed on Iraq .
The Iraqi News Agency quoted an Iraqi official spokesman as saying that Iraq has said time and again that it has implemented to the full the U.N. Security Council Resolution 687 on the issue of POWs .
Iraq has honored all its commitments under the Three-Party Committee on the Missing People during the 1991 Gulf War , said the spokesman .
Kuwait has alleged that Iraq still detains 500 Kuwaiti POWs , but Iraq has flatly denied it .
